  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Integrated Humanitarian Response in Borno and Yobe</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The action will respond to immediate needs within the nutrition and health and WaSH sectors. The project will follow a participatory and community-focused approach to ensure that the beneficiaries are involved in the project design and implementation from day one, and that their resilience is strengthened in the face of future disasters and emergencies. The project aims to improve nutrition security of most vulnerable populations in Borno and Yobe through an integrated nutrition and WaSH response.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">While food is also a major need, other actors are already covering this need. The proposed intervention will aim to support efforts to reduce malnutrition rates in the targeted areas by providing nutrition-specific support as well as access to water and improving sanitation and care practices, thereby adapting a holistic approach to improve the nutritional status of children under five and pregnant/lactating women. WaSH activities will aim to reduce incidence of waterborne diseases by improving access to safe drinking water and sanitation. This will be achieved by planning and implementing activities to raise awareness and improve understanding of application of WaSH practices, improve access to adequate and safe water supply, encourage usage of excreta disposal facilities and promote adoption of hand washing practices.</narrative>
  </description>
